"""
DB-to-File ETL Service - Production-Ready Database Export Microservice

This service exports data from relational databases to various file formats with:
- Full validation (Avro schemas)
- Data transformation (JOLT)
- Value formatting (dates, decimals)
- Multiple file formats (CSV, TSV, Fixed-Width)
- Compression support
- Audit trail via Kafka

Service Port: 9091
Base URL: http://localhost:9091
Framework: FastAPI + AsyncIO
Language: Python 3.11+

Key Features:
-------------
1. Database Reading
   - Streaming query execution (memory-efficient)
   - WHERE clause filtering (12 operators)
   - Column selection and mapping
   - Batch processing

2. File Writing
   - Delimited Files: CSV, TSV, custom delimiters
   - Fixed-Width Files: Positional data with alignment
   - Gzip compression support
   - Custom encoding (UTF-8, Latin-1, etc.)
   - Header row support

3. Value Formatting
   - Date formatting (%Y-%m-%d, %m/%d/%Y, etc.)
   - Decimal formatting (%.2f, %.4f, etc.)
   - Type conversion (string, int, float, decimal, date, datetime)
   - Null literal handling

4. Data Transformation
   - JOLT transformation integration
   - Avro schema validation
   - Column mapping with defaults

5. Audit & Observability
   - Kafka audit events
   - Structured JSON logging
   - Prometheus metrics
   - Correlation ID tracking

Endpoints:
----------
- POST /export/dbtofile - Main export endpoint
- GET /health - Health check
- GET /metrics - Prometheus metrics

For detailed API documentation, see DB_TO_FILE_SPECIFICATION.md
"""

